name: What If I Can Fly
description:
The first thing I want to try is to touch the clouds, just to realize it's all just water and it will probably just go through my fingers. Then I'll look below and all I can see is just roofs of houses that I didn't know the story of. It's probably lonely and cold too. Now I understand why birds fly and still choose to land, why butterflies fly in just a short period during their life cycle because real life happens on the ground. Human interaction is something that I should not take for granted. Down here, life is so much more meaningful.

watercolor on paper & digital illustration
